{
  "stem": "16473.3",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "But they had to leave their child in Czechoslovakia because they were afraid that the child would be a burden to the American sponsor or whatever-- was afraid that the child would be a burden and they couldn't work.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "So that child was left in Czechoslovakia for two years and came out later.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "Anyway, this uncle co-sponsored us in Madison, New York.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "And then we came to Chicago.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "And one of my aunt's first comments to me was, you've suffered enough as a Jew.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "Don't tell them you are a Jew.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I go, OK, because you know I'm already, I've already heard about Jesus.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I'm already interested in that, I've been a Catholic.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You know, I've never really been a Jew in terms of a practicing Jew.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So, OK.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So then the question was what religion to be.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And again, this old tricksterism that I learned, I guess.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I go to the girl that I played with.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "She asks me what religion are you.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I go, what religion are you, I don't know how to say it in English.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "She says Lutheran, I said, yeah, that's what I am, I'm Lutheran.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So I became a Lutheran, long enough until I was 13, when you no longer go to Sunday school and you no longer hear the stories, but you're supposed to go to church.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And in church, the-- the minister starts doing this hell stone and brimstone whatever.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And I go up to him very promptly after that message and I say, you can't tell me that millions of millions of Jews that don't believe in Jesus are going to go to hell, can you.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I mean, I didn't say you can't tell me.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "You know, do you believe?",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
